<subSubSection id="C373656FFFD4C80D3EE6E1FA69B99F16" pageId="0" pageNumber="553" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BD636E4FFD4C80D3EE6E1FA6F159E81" blockId="0.[166,620,1673,1700]" box="[166,620,1673,1700]" pageId="0" pageNumber="553">
<heading id="D09E8188FFD4C80D3EE6E1FA6F159E81" box="[166,620,1673,1700]" fontSize="36" level="2" pageId="0" pageNumber="553" reason="3">
<taxonomicName id="4C694D67FFD4C80D3EE6E1FA6F159E81" authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[166,620,1673,1700]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Pseudoips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prasinana">
<emphasis id="B91DEAF6FFD4C80D3EE6E1FA6CD99E86" bold="true" box="[166,416,1673,1700]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="553">Pseudoips prasinana</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 1758)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD636E4FFD4C80D3E9BE1C969B99F16" blockId="0.[166,1225,1721,1844]" pageId="0" pageNumber="553">
D e s c r i p t i o n. Egg subspherical, flattened (
<figureCitation id="13522A61FFD4C80D3CB1E1CA6E379EF1" box="[753,846,1721,1748]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[174,207,1699,1721]" captionTargetBox="[174,1233,174,1669]" captionTargetId="figure-5@1.[174,1233,174,1672]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1–6. Eggs of Nolidae, Chloephorinae: 1–5 — Pseudoips prasinana. Eggs of Erebidae, Hermeniinae: 6 — Pechipogo strigilata. Scale bars: 1, 3, 6 — 100 µm; 2, 5 — 1000 µm; 4 — 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453436" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453436/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="553">fig. 1, 2</figureCitation>
), height 
<quantity id="4C919B01FFD4C80D3DF9E1CA696E9EF1" box="[953,1047,1721,1748]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="0" pageNumber="553" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
, diameter 
<quantity id="4C919B01FFD4C80D3AD6E1CA6C6B9ED1" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.175" metricValueMax="1.25" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="0" pageNumber="553" unit="mm" value="1.175" valueMax="1.25" valueMin="1.1">1.1– 1.25 mm</quantity>
(n = 2). Egg pale citron colour. As egg develops it becomes dark yellow with brownish-red spot at apical part of egg and same interrupted stripe on perimeter of its medial part. Before caterpillar emergence egg becomes wine red. Chorion white, translucent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF16666CFFD5C80C3EEEE1D06EE19EF1" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453436" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6453436" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453436/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="554" startId="1.[174,207,1699,1721]" targetBox="[174,1233,174,1669]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph id="8BD636E4FFD5C80C3EEEE1D06EE19EF1" blockId="1.[174,1232,1699,1748]" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">
Fig. 1–6. Eggs of 
<taxonomicName id="4C694D67FFD5C80C3F19E1D06CDE9E9C" box="[345,423,1699,1721]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Nolidae</taxonomicName>
, Chloephorinae: 1–5 — 
<taxonomicName id="4C694D67FFD5C80C3CD8E1D06E249E9C" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[664,861,1699,1721]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Pseudoips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prasinana">
<emphasis id="B91DEAF6FFD5C80C3CD8E1D06E249E9C" box="[664,861,1699,1721]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">Pseudoips prasinana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Eggs of 
<taxonomicName id="4C694D67FFD5C80C3DF9E1D069699E9C" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[953,1040,1699,1721]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Erebidae</taxonomicName>
, Hermeniinae: 6 — 
<taxonomicName id="4C694D67FFD5C80C3EEEE1CD6C1E9EF6" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[174,359,1726,1747]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Pechipogo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="strigilata">
<emphasis id="B91DEAF6FFD5C80C3EEEE1CD6C1E9EF6" box="[174,359,1726,1747]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">Pechipogo strigilata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Scale bars: 1, 3, 6 — 100 µm; 2, 5 — 1000 µm; 4 — 10 µm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C373656FFFD5C80F3EEEE19A6CDA9AB0" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="555" pageId="1" pageNumber="554" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD636E4FFD5C80C3EEEE19A69459F3C" blockId="1.[174,1232,1769,1817]" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">
Рис. 1–6. Яйца 
<taxonomicName id="4C694D67FFD5C80C3F14E19A6CDB9EDA" box="[340,418,1769,1791]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Nolidae</taxonomicName>
, Chloephorinae: 1–5 — 
<taxonomicName id="4C694D67FFD5C80C3CDCE19A6E1D9EDB" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[668,868,1769,1790]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Pseudoips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prasinana">
<emphasis id="B91DEAF6FFD5C80C3CDCE19A6E1D9EDB" box="[668,868,1769,1790]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">Pseudoips prasinana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Яйца 
<taxonomicName id="4C694D67FFD5C80C3DF2E19A69709EDA" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[946,1033,1769,1791]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Erebidae</taxonomicName>
, Hermeniinae: 6 — 
<taxonomicName id="4C694D67FFD5C80C3EEEE0706C1E9F3D" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[174,359,1795,1816]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Pechipogo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="strigilata">
<emphasis id="B91DEAF6FFD5C80C3EEEE0706C1E9F3D" box="[174,359,1795,1816]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">Pechipogo strigilata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Масштабные линейки: 1, 3, 6 — 100 мкм; 2, 5 — 1000 мкм; 4 — 10 мкм.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD636E4FFD6C80F3E9BE7DC6F71998F" blockId="2.[166,1225,175,426]" pageId="2" pageNumber="555">
Chorion ridged, marked on two thirds surface. Micropylar area specific, sharply expressed, represented by rosette and 1 row of petalled cells (
<figureCitation id="13522A61FFD6C80F3D35E7BC6EAC98CF" box="[885,981,207,234]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[174,207,1699,1721]" captionTargetBox="[174,1233,174,1669]" captionTargetId="figure-5@1.[174,1233,174,1672]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1–6. Eggs of Nolidae, Chloephorinae: 1–5 — Pseudoips prasinana. Eggs of Erebidae, Hermeniinae: 6 — Pechipogo strigilata. Scale bars: 1, 3, 6 — 100 µm; 2, 5 — 1000 µm; 4 — 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453436" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453436/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="555">fig. 3, 4</figureCitation>
). Rosette clearly expressed with 14–16 long and narrow petalled cells. Secondary cells with sharply expressed distal edges. Resulting micropylar area rounded by raised ring. There are 7–8 of the 32– 35 longitudinal ridges radiate from cells of micropylar area. Longest ridges slightly wavy, with high comb, especially at apical part of egg. Transverse walls less distinct and narrow than ridges (
<figureCitation id="13522A61FFD6C80F3F7BE61C6C0099AF" box="[315,377,367,394]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[174,207,1699,1721]" captionTargetBox="[174,1233,174,1669]" captionTargetId="figure-5@1.[174,1233,174,1672]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1–6. Eggs of Nolidae, Chloephorinae: 1–5 — Pseudoips prasinana. Eggs of Erebidae, Hermeniinae: 6 — Pechipogo strigilata. Scale bars: 1, 3, 6 — 100 µm; 2, 5 — 1000 µm; 4 — 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453436" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453436/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="555">fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Aeropyles clearly expressed. Chorion folded everywhere, especially in the area of micropylar rosette.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD636E4FFD6C80F3E9BE6C96CB399D1" blockId="2.[166,1225,442,661]" pageId="2" pageNumber="555">S h a p e o f g n a w e d h o l e s i n e g g s. Caterpillars nibble out large rounded opening at apical area of eggs.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD636E4FFD6C80F3E9BE6896D959A11" blockId="2.[166,1225,442,661]" pageId="2" pageNumber="555">O v i p o s i t i o n. Eggs laid in single-layer tight clusters where they pressed one to another.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD636E4FFD6C80F3E9BE5496CDA9AB0" blockId="2.[166,1225,442,661]" pageId="2" pageNumber="555">
R e m a r k. Egg shape, micropylar area and form of gnawed holes in eggs similar to those in some species of subfamilies Xyleninae (
<taxonomicName id="4C694D67FFD6C80F3C95E5296ED79A51" authorityName="Schiffermuller" authorityYear="1776" box="[725,942,602,628]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Conistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubiginea">
<emphasis id="B91DEAF6FFD6C80F3C95E5296ED79A51" box="[725,942,602,628]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="555">Conistra rubiginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C694D67FFD6C80F3DB0E52969F09A51" box="[1008,1161,602,628]" class="Insecta" family="Acronictinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Аcronictinae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF84B15FFD6C80F3AD8E5296C369AB1" author="Dolinskaya, I. V." pageId="2" pageNumber="555" pagination="41 - 56" refId="ref2882" refString="Dolinskaya, I. V. The chorionic sculpture of the eggs of some Xyleninae (Lepidoptera, Noctuidae) // Vestnik zoologii. - 2011. - 45, N 1. - P. 41 - 56." type="journal article" year="2011">Dolinskaya, 2011</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF84B15FFD6C80F3F19E5096CEE9AB0" author="Dolinskaya, I. V." box="[345,407,634,661]" pageId="2" pageNumber="555" pagination="353 - 364" refId="ref2922" refString="Dolinskaya, I. V. Egg morphology of some Noctuidae (Lepidoptera) // Vestnik zoologii. - 2014. - 48, N 4. - P. 353 - 364." type="journal article" year="2014">2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
